posts.raw_content:
---
Part 1:  Debundle FEDERAL from STATE/LOCAL elections

Now there are 2 ballots.  Federal ballot.  State ballot.  Complete and total severance of ballot AND process (including tally)

---
Part 2: Order the FEC to manage at all local levels.  This is an enormous challenge.  You'd need probably 50,000 new employees, and 50,000 centers to rent for a day or 3.

Who pays for all this?  States pay.  They pay because the Federal government will DEDUCT COSTS of this system from the States funding across the board.  So every single solitary grant will have a deduction, and the red deduction line item will be *"Federal elections costs"*

---
Part 3: Voting day.   FEC election officials administer FEDERAL ballots at the election venue

(FEC employees, OR US military contracted off-duty by FEC in a civilian capacity -- 9 day thing, 3 days training, 3 days administering, 3 days other)

FEC election officials DO NOT participate in State / Local elections, processes and do not touch their ballots

And VICE VERSA.

They may share a venue and voting time, but that's it.  There needs to be strict partitioning.

---
Part 4: (Possibly as a separate EO) :   the FEC REQUIRES proof of US citizenship and residency.   The residency requirement is because of the electoral nature of the federal election. One is BOUND to their state for the popular vote (which selects ELECTORS who do the real presidential vote).

This is a Drivers License with Real ID; some other REAL ID thing given by state; proof of residency (a utility bill) if you don' thave a state license.   DL is all you need.  SSN card and other photo ID would be sufficient.
